<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-05-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-05-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="265" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d265">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">800.51W89/954</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Economic Adviser</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Feis</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-05-31">May 31,
                                1935</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The President has given his approval to the form of the June 15 debt
                            notes and to the further suggestion that the idea of payments in kind
                            and special materials might be broached to the British and Belgian
                            Ambassadors. All the debt notices have been sent to CR<note n="9" xml:id="d265fn9">Division of Coordination and Review.</note> for <pb facs="0482" n="380" xml:id="pg_380"/> despatch in the regular way.
                            You may wish to ask the Ambassadors to come in to talk with you early
                            next week.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>H[<hi rend="smallcaps">erbert</hi>] F[<hi rend="smallcaps">eis</hi>]</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>